Experimento 1 - Biocontrole F√∫ngico

Carrega os pacotes necess√°rios

Passos para realiza√ß√£o da an√°lise dos dados: 1 - Realizar an√°lises explorat√≥rias para verificar o comportamento da vari√°vel a ser analisada; 2 - Nesse passo s√£o realizadas as an√°lises pr√≥priamente ditas.

Carregar os dados

data1 <- read.csv("Biocontrole.csv", row.names = 1)
data1

Passo 1 - Realizar uma an√°lise explorat√≥ria dos dados

Plotar um histograma para verificar a distribui√ß√£o poss√≠vel dos dados

hist1 <- ggplot(data1, aes(data1$growth)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 20) +
  labs(x = "Colony diameter (cm)", y = "Frequency") +
  geom_density(col = 'red')


ggsave(
  plot = hist1,
  filename = "Figures/Experimento_1/Histograma1.svg",
  #height = 5,
  width = 8
)


hist1

Verificar o ajuste √† normalidade univariada e homogeneidade das vari√¢ncias

# Normalidade univariada
shapiro.test(data1$growth)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  data1$growth
## W = 0.96426, p-value = 0.001123
# Homogeneidade das vari√¢ncias
bartlett.test(growth ~ group, data = data1)
## 
##  Bartlett test of homogeneity of variances
## 
## data:  growth by group
## Bartlett's K-squared = Inf, df = 44, p-value < 2.2e-16

Passo 2 - Considerando que a hip√≥tese de normalidade dos dados testada durante a an√°lise de Shapiro-Wilk foi rejeitada (p = 0.001123), ser√° utilizado o logar√≠tmo na base 10 do crescimento micelial como vari√°vel resposta. Desse modo, a normalidade dos res√≠duos dever√° ser testada para verificar a ader√™ncia dos dados ao modelo.

Roda a an√°lise de vari√¢ncia

lmModel <- aov(
  
  # F√≥rmula utilizada no ajuste linear
  log10(growth) ~ group,
  
  # Dataset utilizado
  data = data1
  
)

summary.aov(lmModel)
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## group       44 0.8293 0.01885   5.053 2.73e-11 ***
## Residuals   93 0.3469 0.00373                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

Testa a normalidade univariada dos res√≠duos

# Normalidade univariada dos res√≠duos
shapiro.test(lmModel$residuals)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  lmModel$residuals
## W = 0.98712, p-value = 0.2261

Gera um histograma com os res√≠duos gerados na an√°lise de vari√¢ncia

res <- data.frame(
  cbind(
    lmModel$residuals,
    lmModel$model 
  )
)


hist2 <- ggplot(res, aes(res$lmModel.residuals)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 20) +
  labs(x = "Residuals", y = "Frequency") +
  geom_density(col = 'red')


ggsave(
  plot = hist2,
  filename = "Figures/Experimento_1/Histograma2.svg",
  width = 8
)


hist2

NOTA: acima pode-se observar que a distribui√ß√£o dos res√≠duos segue uma distibui√ß√£o normal e que a hip√≥tese de ader√™ncia a normalidade n√£o foi rejeitada, desse modo pode-se considerar os resultados da an√°lise de vari√¢ncia (ANOVA) como representativos dos dados, e portanto, satisfat√≥ria.

Gera o teste de multiplicidade

hsd_pair <- LSD.test(
  lmModel, 
  "group",
  group = T,
  p.adj = 'bonferroni'
)

Plota o boxplot com os dados do experimento 1

stat_labels = hsd_pair$groups

stat_labels$labels = paste0(stat_labels$groups, " (", round(stat_labels$`log10(growth)` * 10, digits = 2), ")")

gp_box <- ggplot(data1, aes(x = reorder(group, growth, mean), y = growth)) +

  # Graph type
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.5) +
  
  # Labels
  labs(x = "Isolate", y = "Colony diameter (cm)") +
  
  # Theme labels position
  theme() +
  
  # Include multiplicity test results as text
  geom_text(
    data = hsd_pair$groups,
    mapping = aes(
      x = rownames(hsd_pair$groups), 
      y = 2, 
      label = stat_labels$groups
    ),
    hjust = 0
  ) +
  
  # Insert horizontal lines
  geom_hline(yintercept = 6, linetype = "dashed", color = "grey50") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 9, size = 0.2, color = "grey50") +
  geom_segment(aes(x = 11, xend = 45, y = 1.8, yend = 1.8), size = 1, color = "grey70") +
  geom_segment(aes(x = 1, xend = 10, y = 1.8, yend = 1.8), size = 1, color = "grey30") +
  
  # Rotate right
  coord_flip()


ggsave(
  plot = gp_box,
  filename = "Figures/Experimento_1/Boxplot.svg",
  height = 10,
  width = 8
)


gp_box

Verificar o ajuste √† normalidade univariada e homogeneidade das vari√¢ncias

# Normalidade univariada
shapiro.test(data2$rootLength)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  data2$rootLength
## W = 0.9649, p-value = 4.383e-09
shapiro.test(data2$area)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  data2$area
## W = 0.86448, p-value < 2.2e-16
# Homogeneidade das vari√¢ncias
bartlett.test(area ~ group, data = data2)
## 
##  Bartlett test of homogeneity of variances
## 
## data:  area by group

## 
##  Bartlett test of homogeneity of variances
## 
## data:  rootLength by group

Final comparison

full_dataset <- merge(
  data1 %>%
  group_by(group) %>%
  summarise(
    mean = mean(growth),
    sd = sd(growth),
    var = var(growth),
    min = min(growth),
    max = max(growth),
    n = n()
  ),
  data2 %>%
  group_by(group) %>%
  summarise(
    mean = mean(rootLength),
    sd = sd(rootLength),
    var = var(rootLength),
    min = min(rootLength),
    max = max(rootLength),
    n = n()
  ),
  by.x = "group",
  by.y = "group"
)


full_scatter <- ggplot(full_dataset, aes(x = mean.x, y = mean.y)) +
  
  # Define theme
  theme_bw() +
  
  
  # Add reference lines
  geom_hline(yintercept = 9, linetype = "dashed", size = 0.8, color = "grey70") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 5.5, linetype = "dashed", size = 0.8, color = "grey70") +
  
  # Labels
  labs(
    x = "Biocontrol variable. Average colony diameter (cm)", 
    y = "Vegetal growth promotion/inhibition. Average root length (cm)") +
  
  # Remove legends
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  
  # Define geometry
  geom_point(aes(color = group), size = 3) +
  
  # Define labels inside graph
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = group,  color = group), size = 5)


ggsave(
  plot = full_scatter,
  filename = "Figures/ScatterplotBiocontrolVsVegetalPromotion.svg",
  height = 10,
  width = 8
)


full_scatter
